main event: On February 12, 1964, a commercial airline pilot observed a brilliant bluish-white light maneuver in front of and below his aircraft while flying at 28,000 feet over central Wisconsin.
interesting points: The object moved rapidly left to right at high speed, paused, and then reversed direction multiple times., The pilot reported the sighting to air traffic control, who confirmed the object was not tracked on radar., Project Blue Book investigated the incident and concluded it was likely a meteor or astronomical phenomenon., A witness from Dayton, Ohio, reported a bright light on February 15, 1964, that disappeared rapidly., Various reports included descriptions of objects ranging in shape and behavior, emphasizing the uncertainty and intrigue around UFO sightings.
